Yobe State governor, Alhaji Ibrahim Gaidam has approved N63.5 million for the provision of Ramadan feeding for the less privileged and for the conduct of Tafsir during the Holy monts of Ramadan.  A statement by the Director-General Press Affairs to the Governor, Malam Abdullahi Bego said the free feeding would be in 42 centers across the 17 local government areas of the state.  Of the amount approved by the governor, Bego said N48.5 million will be used for the purchase of rams and cooking condiments for the 42 feeding centres while N15 million will be used for the payment of allowances to Muslim preachers who will seek to guide the Muslim faithful through the Holy Month.  "His Excellency the governor had also approved 1, 260 bags of rice and 630 jerry cans of cooking oil to be used in the 42 designated feeding centres during Ramadan", he explained.